from keras.models import Sequential
from keras.layers import Dense, Conv2D, MaxPool2D , Flatten
model = Sequential()
model.add(Conv2D(input_shape=(224,224,3),filters=64,kernel_size=(3,3),padding="same", activation="relu"))
model.add(Conv2D(filters=64,kernel_size=(3,3),padding="same", activation="relu"))
model.add(MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2),strides=(2,2)))
model.add(Conv2D(filters=128, kernel_size=(3,3), padding="same", activation="relu"))
model.add(Conv2D(filters=128, kernel_size=(3,3), padding="same", activation="relu"))
model.add(MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2),strides=(2,2)))
model.add(Conv2D(filters=256, kernel_size=(3,3), padding="same", activation="relu"))
model.add(Conv2D(filters=256, kernel_size=(3,3), padding="same", activation="relu"))
model.add(Conv2D(filters=256, kernel_size=(3,3), padding="same", activation="relu"))
model.add(MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2),strides=(2,2)))
model.add(Conv2D(filters=512, kernel_size=(3,3), padding="same", activation="relu"))
model.add(Conv2D(filters=512, kernel_size=(3,3), padding="same", activation="relu"))
model.add(Conv2D(filters=512, kernel_size=(3,3), padding="same", activation="relu"))
model.add(MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2),strides=(2,2)))
model.add(Conv2D(filters=512, kernel_size=(3,3), padding="same", activation="relu"))
model.add(Conv2D(filters=512, kernel_size=(3,3), padding="same", activation="relu"))
model.add(Conv2D(filters=512, kernel_size=(3,3), padding="same", activation="relu"))
model.add(MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2),strides=(2,2)))
model.add(Flatten())
model.summary()

                  include_top=False,
                  input_shape=(224, 224, 3))

We now load the images and true labels¶

In [26]:
from keras.preprocessing import image
from keras.applications.vgg16 import preprocess_input
import numpy as np
import os
import pandas as pd

image_dir = "/content/drive/MyDrive/Flower_images"

image_files = [os.path.join(image_dir, f) for f in os.listdir(image_dir) if os.path.isfile(os.path.join(image_dir, f))]
features_list = []
df = pd.read_csv("/content/drive/MyDrive/flower_labels.csv")
y = []

for img_path in image_files:
    img = image.load_img(img_path,target_size=(224,224))
    selected_row = (df[df['file'] == img_path[-8:]])
    label = selected_row['label'].iloc[0]
    y.append(label)
    # print(label)
    x = image.img_to_array(img)
    # print(x.shape)
    x = np.expand_dims(x,axis = 0)
    # print(x.shape)
    x = preprocess_input(x)
    # print(x.shape)
    features = conv_base.predict(x)
    # print(features.shape)
    # print(f"feature vector shape is : {features.shape}")
    features_list.append(features)

from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
feature_vectors = np.array(features_list)
print(feature_vectors.shape)
feature_vectors = np.reshape(feature_vectors, (210, -1))
print(feature_vectors.shape)
pca = PCA(n_components=2,
          svd_solver='randomized',
          random_state=42)

reduced_feature_vectors_2d = pca.fit_transform(feature_vectors)

print(reduced_feature_vectors_2d.shape)

from sklearn.manifold import TSNE

tsne = TSNE(n_components=2,  # Number of components to reduce to
            perplexity=30,    # The perplexity hyperparameter (suggested range: 5 to 50)
            learning_rate=50,  # The learning rate hyperparameter (suggested range: 10 to 1000)
            n_iter=2000,     # Number of iterations (suggested range: 250 to 1000)
            random_state=42)  # Random seed for reproducibility

reduced_feature_vectors_2d_tsne = tsne.fit_transform(feature_vectors)

from sklearn.cluster import KMeans

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
num_clusters = 10
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=num_clusters,n_init=10)
kmeans.fit(reduced_feature_vectors_2d)
cluster_labels = kmeans.labels_

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
for cluster in range(num_clusters):
    plt.scatter(reduced_feature_vectors_2d[cluster_labels == cluster, 0], reduced_feature_vectors_2d[cluster_labels == cluster, 1], label=f'Cluster {cluster+1}')
plt.title('Reduced and Clustered Data Points(K_means)')
plt.xlabel('Principal Component 1')
plt.ylabel('Principal Component 2')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

dbscan = DBSCAN(eps=165, min_samples=1)

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
unique_labels = np.unique(cluster_labels)
for label in unique_labels:
    if label == -1:  # Noise points
        plt.scatter(reduced_feature_vectors_2d[cluster_labels == label, 0], reduced_feature_vectors_2d[cluster_labels == label, 1], color='gray', label='Noise')
    else:
        plt.scatter(reduced_feature_vectors_2d[cluster_labels == label, 0], reduced_feature_vectors_2d[cluster_labels == label, 1], label=f'Cluster {label}')
plt.title('Reduced and Clustered Data Points (DBSCAN)')
plt.xlabel('Principal Component 1')
plt.ylabel('Principal Component 2')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

Silhouette and Homogenity score between the reduced kmeans labels and true labels¶

import pandas as pd
from sklearn.metrics import homogeneity_score

csv_file_path = "/content/drive/MyDrive/flower_labels.csv"
cluster_labels_df = pd.read_csv(csv_file_path)

true_labels = cluster_labels_df["label"].values
print(y, kmeans.labels_)

Method here for determinning the number of clusters is Elbow method. For doing so, we can pick a result cluster number that the WCSS differences after which are negligible.¶

In [50]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score

k_values = range(2, 21)
wcss_scores = []
silhouette_scores = []

for k in k_values:
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42, n_init=10)
    kmeans.fit(reduced_feature_vectors_2d)
    wcss_scores.append(kmeans.inertia_)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.plot(k_values, wcss_scores, marker='o')
plt.xlabel('Number of Clusters (k)')
plt.ylabel('Within-Cluster Sum of Squares (WCSS)')
plt.title('Elbow Method')


plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
